rComments: Lectures were straightforward, concise, and quite short (usually 30 minutes to 1.5 hours per week). Dr. Thivierge also provided practice quizzes and exams. We were graded based on weekly labs and a midterm and final. The labs were easy and had a max of 1 page. The exams were 24-hour take home and reflected the content we learned in class.

If you like asynchronous classes you'll really like this prof. His class was super well organized and reasonably paced, he also provided a lot of good examples. Didn't need to use the textbook at all. It was an easy A with open book tests and easy labs. Hard to tell if how his class would be in person but I'd definitely give it a shot.

I am not very good at math but his short videos explaining each concept were very clear and easy to understand, he also posted videos with examples on how to do all of the equations which was very helpful. Would definitely take this prof again.
Ive never liked math, especially stats, but I love this class. His lectures are short and simple and he explains SUPER well. I would definitely recommend :)
An easy A, better than other Uottawa stats profs in my opinion

I'm terrible at math and got an A. Prof breaks down each lecture into multiple short videos, around 5-10 minutes, none of his lectures was over 50 minutes. Midterm & exam were open book. Prof replied to emails within 24 hours, usually faster. The only downside is that we barely got practice problems outside of the one or two he'd solve in lectures.

Prof Thivierge adapted this statistics course for online really well. It was asynchronous so you can work through the material whenever you are free. His lectures were incredibly easy to understand and covered all of the test material, so I never needed to buy the textbook. Definitely recommend his class!
He made online learning very simple. The assessments are fair and ask you exactly what you need to know.
Super prof!! I would recommend Pr Thivierge 100%!! He made me understand & enjoy stats, which is NOT an easy task!! Plus his assistant was really nice & helpful with the labs!!

Made stats class super enjoyable, understandable and most importantly, fun AND easy. Everything was online which was very convenient. Who doesnt like learning from the comfort of their own home? Answers all emails and questions within hours. Always accessible outside of class. Clear grading for labs and exams. Very fair exams. The BEST, take him

Not the best prof honestly. He was hardly ever accessible outside of class so it was difficult when I had issues with the course material. The course itself was very easy, doesn't require much effort. But, because it was online, I felt like the prof was super disconnected from the course and didn't make much of an effort.

J'ai beaucoup aimé mon cours de méthode de recherche avec ce prof car le cours était bien organisé, intéressant, utile. Les critères d'examens était clair. Le travail de session est difficile mais il vaut la peine de s'y investir. Dr Thivierge prépare bien ses cours et se préoccupe de maintenir une bonne qualité d'enseignement.

For a stats class I thought I'd fail, it was amazing. I finished with an A- and it was thanks to this prof. He is hilarious and really nice to students and he is always willing to re-explain every single time until it's understood. Wish I could have him again! Definitely take it!

I really liked this prof. As long as you go over the notes, the midterm and the exam should get you a good mark. His labs are pretty much a guaranteed 100% (there are three) if you do them properly. No textbook. He is always willing to go over material again if you don't understand. I would definitely take another class with him if I could!

Genuinely a caring professor. A class like stats can be intimidating but Dr.Thivierge makes it all understandable with his AMAZING slides. They are hands down the best class slides I have ever seen for a class at Uottawa. He also wants the class to do very well so he gives great practice resources. Definitely recommend him for this class!
Very clear and helpful. Always available for questions as his office, I recomend his class !

Great prof! Made all the confusing concepts easy, and went over them until everyone in the class understood. No textbook. Very charismatic and personable, and willing to listen to class complaints and change to make the class a better experience. If you have to take stats, take it with him!

Amazing teacher. He made the tough material as easy a possible and was always willing to spend extra time on a concept if someone was having trouble. Exams and midterms were straightforward and if you keep up with the work and concepts you'll do great! Also doesn't require you buying a textbook!
The best professor at the university of ottawa hands down! Made everything so easy to understand and is the nicest guy ever. I dreaded having to take stats but he made me like it! And no textbook!
Pretty good prof. A little boring but he does know his stuff. Slides and course material is helpful and you don't need the textbook. He's pretty helpful if you need after class help.

Great professor. He was my 4th year undergraduate honours thesis prof. Very nice, not vain unlike soo many other profs, very helpful and understanding. He will do anything for you, and will take into consideration all of your ideas. Such a kind heart and wonderful person.

MEILLEUR PROF!! pour une classe de methode de recherche, je pourrais vraiment pas demander de plus. SUPER flexible, les examples donnee en classes sont super bon et drole, a un sense d'humeur, est VRAIMENT clair pour ce qu'il demande, c'est examens sont facile et reflete la matiere du cours. Fortement suggeree, un de mes meilleur profs.

Il comprend bien sa matière mais a parfois de la difficulté à nous la transmettre, souvent des erreurs dans les powerpoint et dans les explications aussi.  Par conte, il fait des quiz et des lab ce qui aide et remontre la moyenne du groupe
